# Workspace-wide pnpm config.
#
# `node-linker=hoisted` produces a flat `node_modules/` layout
# (yarn / npm-classic style) instead of pnpm's default symlink-store
# isolation. Required for the mobile package: Expo's CLI + Metro
# plugins assume transitive deps (`expo-asset`, `expo-modules-core`,
# etc.) are resolvable from the package root, and EAS Build runs
# `pnpm install` from the workspace root — so a package-level
# `.npmrc` doesn't take effect there.
#
# Trade-off: PWA loses pnpm's strict isolation and could surface
# phantom-dep usage. In practice it's fine — PWA's deps are well-
# scoped and we don't rely on the strictness as a correctness check.
node-linker=hoisted
